  "topic_name": "Measurement",
  "canonical_explanation": {
    "text": "Measurement is the process of comparing an unknown quantity with a standard unit. Standard units are fixed and universally accepted, making measurements consistent everywhere. The International System of Units (SI) is the globally accepted system. The SI unit of length is meter (m), of mass is kilogram (kg), and of time is second (s). We use rulers and measuring tapes to measure length, balances to measure mass, and clocks or stopwatches to measure time. Accurate measurement requires proper technique and reading scales correctly.",
    "rules": [
      "Measurement compares an unknown quantity with a standard unit.",
      "SI unit of length is meter (m).",
      "SI unit of mass is kilogram (kg).",
      "SI unit of time is second (s).",
      "1 meter = 100 centimeters = 1000 millimeters.",
      "1 kilometer = 1000 meters.",
      "1 kilogram = 1000 grams.",
      "1 hour = 60 minutes = 3600 seconds.",
      "Read scales at eye level to avoid parallax error.",
      "Standard units allow for consistent measurements worldwide."
    ]
  },
